SIMPLE: hibernaculum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hibernaculum
<hw>Hi`ber*nac"u*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Hibernacle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A winter
bud, in which the rudimentary foliage or flower, as of most trees and
shrubs in the temperate zone, is protected by closely overlapping
scales.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A little case in which certain
insects pass the winter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Winter home or abiding place.</def> <rj><au>J.
Burroughs.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hibernal</ent>⟦br⟧
